    "The key components of this tool are the search space, the search algorithm, and the scoring function.",
    "In REINVENT 2.0, a generative model is used as the search space.",
    "REINVENT 2.0 is trained using data obtained from ChEMBL and exhibits the capability to generate compounds in the SMILES format.",
    "The tool uses reinforcement learning as the search algorithm, which is responsible for generating candidate molecules.",
    "The algorithm receives rewards based on the prediction scores per candidate, where the scores are based on several parameters such as calculated properties, pharmacophore shape, similarity criteria, etc."
